HEADWORD: Whirlbat
<hw>Whirl"bat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anything moved with
a whirl, as preparatory for a blow, or to augment the force of it; --
applied by poets to the cestus of ancient boxers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>whirlbat</qex> and the rapid race shall be⟦br⟧
Reserved for Caesar.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whirl-blast</ent>⟦br⟧
